The Zamfara State Police Public Relations Officer, SP Mohammed Shehu, in a statement made available to SaharaReporters said that on January 1, 2023, there was a report of the abduction of some commuters along Tsafe-Gusau Road. The police in Zamfara State, Northwest Nigeria on Thursday rescued 15 kidnap Victims including seven women, six men and two children.  The Zamfara State Police Public Relations Officer, SP Mohammed Shehu, in a statement made available to SaharaReporters said that on January 1, 2023, there was a report of the abduction of some commuters along Tsafe-Gusau Road.  Acting on the report, the state police command deployed additional Police Tactical Operatives to the location for a search and rescue operation, through which the victims were rescued, Shehu said.  Shehu said while narrating their ordeal, the victims told the police that they were blocked and abducted by a large number of terrorists along Yankara-Tsafe-Gusau Road by Magazu village while coming back from Abuja and Kaduna, and heading to Gusau, Sokoto and Birnin Kebbi.  He said the victims were medically checked at the police clinic facility, debriefed by the police detectives and thereafter reunited with their families and relations.  "The Commissioner of Police, CP Kolo Yusuf, congratulated the rescued victims for regaining their freedom, and assured police continuous commitment to sustain the ongoing search operation in order to rescue the remaining victims in captivity," he added.